I have successfully identified and fixed the bug in the Commons Math SimplexTableau class. Here's the summary of what I did:

## Problem Analysis
The issue was in the `getSolution()` method of `SimplexTableau.java` related to MATH-781. When variables are unrestricted (can be negative), the algorithm introduces a special "x-" column to represent the negative component of the solution. The problem occurred when a decision variable was basic in the objective function row (row 0).

## The Bug
In the original code:
```java
if (basicRow != null && basicRow == 0) {
    // if the basic row is found to be the objective function row
    // set the coefficient to 0 -> this case handles unconstrained
    // variables that are still part of the objective function
    coefficients[i] = 0;
}
```

When a variable was basic in the objective function row, the code would set its value to 0 without considering the negative variable adjustment that should apply when `restrictToNonNegative` is false.

