```java
if (basicRow != null && basicRow == 0) {
    // if the basic row is found to be the objective function row
    // set the coefficient to 0, but account for negative variable adjustment
    coefficients[i] = 0 - (restrictToNonNegative ? 0 : mostNegative);
}
```

## Result
The fix ensures that when unrestricted variables are allowed, the negative variable adjustment is consistently applied to all variables in the solution extraction, including those that happen to be basic in the objective function row. This maintains mathematical correctness of the transformation used for handling unrestricted variables in the Simplex algorithm.

